subSubSection.paragraph:
Pleopods (
Fig. 1
) each with relatively slender protopods. Endopod of first pleopod (
Fig. 3H
) elongate, spatulate, slightly shorter than exopod. Second to fifth pleopods becoming shorter posteriorly; each endopod well-developed, 0.70-0.80 length of each exopod, lacking appendix interna (
Fig. 3I
).

Protopod of uropod (
Fig.2G
) stout; posterolateral projection blunt. Endopod of uropod (
Fig. 2G
) moderately narrow, slightly longer than exopod, overreaching tip of telson, tapering distally; exopod (
Fig. 2G
) falling short of tip of telson, lateral margin nearly straight, terminating in minute tooth partially obscured by tuft of short setae; posterior margin roundly truncate; very short diaeresis evident.

